net.hudup.core.evaluate

Class CosineTwoArrayMetricValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.evaluate.TwoArrayMetricValue
      • net.hudup.core.evaluate.CosineTwoArrayMetricValue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, MetricValue

    public class CosineTwoArrayMetricValue
extends TwoArrayMetricValue
    This abstract class represents a cosine of two arrays of real numbers (cosine of two real vectors) as a MetricValue. Note, MetricValue interface represents value of a metric, which can be anything. Because this class extends directly TwoArrayMetricValue, it also contains two arrays of real numbers (two real vectors). Moreover, its value() method returns the cosine of such two vectors.

    10.0
